    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-01-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-01-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="804"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d804">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.00/1145</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Greek Minister (<persName type="from"
                            >Diamantopoulos</persName>) to the Chief of the Division of Near Eastern
                        Affairs (<persName type="to">Murray</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-01-08">January 8,
                            1942</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Murray</hi>: From certain Greek quarters anxious
                    to show loyalty and devotion to the United States in their war effort, and their
                    willingness to make any sacrifice for the common cause, I have been asked to
                    inquire if the formations of Greek volunteer units will be agreeable to the
                    United States Military Authorities.</p>
                <pb facs="0822" n="816" xml:id="pg_816"/>
                <p>I should be much obliged, my dear Mr. Murray, if you kindly informed me
                    accordingly.</p>
                <p>With my kind personal regards,</p>
                <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>C. <hi rend="smallcaps">Diamantopoulos</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
